   289	// snapshot returns a faithful repaint of the emulator's current screen: a byte
   290	// sequence that reconstructs the exact visible grid (with SGR attributes),
   291	// alt-screen mode, and cursor position when written to a fresh terminal. This
   292	// replaces the old raw-scrollback replay, which could not rebuild a long-lived
   293	// full-screen TUI because the bytes that set up the alt screen had already aged
   294	// out of the byte window.
   295	//
   296	// Must be called with t.mu held.
   297	func (t *sessionTerminal) snapshot() []byte {
